Key Learnings

Tokens

- LLMs process tokens, not words.

Embeddings

- Convert text into vectors representing semantic meaning.

Transformer

- Processes relationships between all tokens simultaneously.

Attention

- Determines which tokens are most relevant.

Context Window

- Defines how much information the model can remember.

Temperature

- Controls randomness of model responses.

Hallucination

- Confidently generated incorrect information.

RAG

- Retrieves external knowledge before generating a response.

